        <h1>Eatly Privacy Policy</h1>

        <div class="highlight">
          <strong>Last updated:</strong> July 2025<br />
          <strong>Effective date:</strong> January 2025
        </div>

        <p>
          Eatly (“we,” “our,” or “us”) is committed to protecting your privacy.
          This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and
          safeguard your information when you use our premium mobile application.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <h3>1.1 Information You Provide</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>User Preferences:</strong> Language settings, quiz
            preferences, and app configuration
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Learning Data:</strong> Quiz results, favorite words, study
            progress, and performance statistics
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Feedback:</strong> User feedback, bug reports, and support
            communications
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>1.2 Information Automatically Collected</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Device Information:</strong> Device type, operating system,
            app version
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Usage Analytics:</strong> Features used, session duration,
            aggregated usage trends
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Performance Data:</strong> Crash reports, loading times, and
            technical diagnostics
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use collected information to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Deliver and maintain the full premium app experience</li>
          <li>Personalize content and recommendations</li>
          <li>Track your learning progress and provide statistics</li>
          <li>Monitor performance and improve stability</li>
          <li>Respond to support requests</li>
          <li>Analyze usage trends to guide product improvements</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Data Storage and Security</h2>
        <p>Your data is stored locally and, if enabled, securely backed up:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Local Storage:</strong> Core app data is stored on your
            device using iOS secure storage mechanisms
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cloud Backup:</strong> Optional iCloud synchronization is
            available for seamless device restoration
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Security:</strong> We use industry-standard safeguards and
            encryption for data in transit and at rest
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Third-Party Services and SDKs</h2>
        <p>The app integrates the following services:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Firebase Analytics (Google):</strong> Usage analytics and
            crash reporting. Collected data: device details, usage statistics,
            crash diagnostics.
            <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank"
              >Privacy Policy</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>App Store Connect (Apple):</strong> Processing of the
            one-time purchase. Collected data: purchase history, payment status.
            <a
              href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/en-ww/"
              target="_blank"
              >Privacy Policy</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>StoreKit (Apple):</strong> Purchase validation and restore
            flows. Collected data: transaction receipts, entitlement status.
            <a
              href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/en-ww/"
              target="_blank"
              >Privacy Policy</a
            >
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell or rent your personal information. Data is shared only:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>With your explicit consent</li>
          <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
          <li>To protect our rights, property, or safety</li>
          <li>
            In aggregated, anonymized form for analytics or performance insights
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You may request to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access your personal data</li>
          <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
          <li>Delete stored data</li>
          <li>Export a copy of your data</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent for optional data processing</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Data Retention Periods</h2>
        <p>We retain information only as long as necessary:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Local App Data:</strong> Stored on your device until you
            delete the app or remove the data from settings
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>iCloud Backup Data:</strong> Retained per your Apple iCloud
            settings and can be removed through Apple services
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Analytics Data:</strong> Retained up to 24 months, then
            anonymized or deleted
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Crash Reports:</strong> Retained up to 12 months for
            diagnostics
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Purchase Records:</strong> Retained up to 7 years to satisfy
            tax and accounting requirements
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Support Communications:</strong> Retained up to 24 months
            after resolution
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You can request deletion of data via app settings or by contacting us
          directly.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Children's Privacy (Under 13)</h2>
        <p>
          Eatly is suitable for users aged 4+ and complies with COPPA and other
          child privacy regulations.
        </p>
        <h3>8.1 Information from Children Under 13</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13
            without verifiable parental consent
          </li>
          <li>
            If unauthorized data is discovered, it is deleted promptly
          </li>
          <li>
            Parents may review, delete, or refuse further collection of their
            child’s data
          </li>
          <li>No personal data from children is used for marketing purposes</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>8.2 Parental Controls and Consent</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Parental consent is required before collecting personal information
            from children under 13
          </li>
          <li>Consent can be withdrawn at any time by contacting us</li>
          <li>Parents have access to their child’s personal information</li>
          <li>Parents can request deletion at any time</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>8.3 Educational Content and Safety</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>The app provides age-appropriate educational content</li>
          <li>No inappropriate advertising is shown to children</li>
          <li>Content filters and safety measures are in place</li>
          <li>No precise geolocation data is collected from children</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>9. Updates to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Material changes are
          communicated in-app or via other appropriate channels.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Contact Information</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Email:</strong> spikedevsup@gmail.com<br />
          <strong>App Store:</strong> Eatly
        </p>
